Liverpool manager, Jurgen Klopp, has ruled out the possibility of Zlatan Ibrahimovic playing for the club. Ibrahimovic has been linked with a move back to Europe, after confirming his departure from LA Galaxy on Wednesday. The 38-year-old moved to MLS from Manchester United and scored 30 times in 29 appearances for Galaxy. Klopp, speaking to Sportbladet, gave his reasons for not wanting Ibrahimovic. “If he had not played for Manchester United before, then we might have considered him. “But I’m not even sure he wanted to play here. We’re a pretty intense team,” Klopp told Sportbladet. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.